really giving such a unique bastion

00:06:57.500 --> 00:07:01.720
from where to teach cooking
and to write about cooking.

00:07:01.720 --> 00:07:06.020
And I feel, when people ask me,
going back to my introduction

00:07:06.020 --> 00:07:08.310
to this question, when people
ask me, "Should I change?

00:07:08.310 --> 00:07:11.240
I've been a lawyer 30 years,"
you know, I say, "Well,

00:07:11.240 --> 00:07:13.340
if you want to be landscaper,

00:07:13.340 --> 00:07:15.330
you know how to negotiate
with your clients."

00:07:15.330 --> 00:07:20.090
You know, like, you never know
when, because life is such a zigzag

00:07:20.090 --> 00:07:26.270
and now I see the value in
not wanting to always go

00:07:26.270 --> 00:07:30.290
in a straight path and
everything make sense.

00:07:30.290 --> 00:07:34.070
And then I think things
naturally started coming together.

00:07:34.070 --> 00:07:35.370
&gt;&gt; Joe Yonana: Yeah.

00:07:35.370 --> 00:07:37.590
You know, it's striking me when
you were talking about being,

00:07:37.590 --> 00:07:43.460
when you first moved to Texas, it's
the expat story really in a way.

00:07:43.460 --> 00:07:47.500
And, you know, I don't know if the
